<%= self_id %>

----TASK----
Review the provided code diff carefully and identify *only* highly confident
issues which are relevant to any code context.

----CODEBASE CHANGES TO REVIEW----
<%= input %>
--------

<%- unless file_lines.to_s.empty? -%>
----ADDITIONAL CONTEXT: FULL FILE CONTENT AFTER APPLYING REVIEWED CHANGES----
<%= file_lines %>
--------
<%- end -%>

----TASK GUIDELINES----
- Only report issues on lines added or modified in the diff above. The full
  file is provided solely as context; do not raise issues about unchanged lines.
- Only report issues you are 100% confident are relevant to any context.
- Never report issues related to software versions, model names, or similar
  details that you believe have not yet been released.
- Only include issues that are significantly valuable to the maintainers (e.g., clearly expressed in the requirements below,
  bugs, security flaws, or clear maintainability concerns).
- Do not report vague, theoretical, or overly generic advice.
<%- if symbol_lookup -%>
- Before reporting that a method, class, or constant is undefined, misspelled,
  or that a third-party library API is used incorrectly, confirm it with the
  symbol lookup tool. Do not assert an API is wrong from memory alone.
- Treat a "No definition found" result as inconclusive, not proof of absence:
  C-extension and other native gem methods often have no indexable definition.
  When you cannot verify a third-party API, do not report it.
<%- end -%>
<%= requirements %>
<%= json_requirements %>

Respond with a JSON object containing an "issues" array following this schema:
{
  "issues": [
    {
      "title": "<issue_title>",
      "details": "<issue_description>",
      "tags": ["<tag1>", "<tag2>", ...],
      "severity": <1-4>,
      "confidence": <1-4>,
      "affected_lines": [
        {
          "start_line": <int>,
          "end_line": <int>,
          "proposal": "<proposed code to replace the affected lines (optional)>"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

- If present, proposal blocks must match the indentation of the original code
  and apply cleanly to lines start_line..end_line.

Available issue tags:
- bug
- security
- performance
- readability
- maintainability
- overcomplexity
- language
- architecture
- compatibility
- deprecation
- anti-pattern
- naming
- code-style

Issue severity scale:
<%= severity_scale %>

Confidence scale:
<%= confidence_scale %>

If no issues are found according to the criteria, respond with an empty list: []
